  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "A 32-year-old man comes to the physician because of a 3-week history of recurrent thumb pain that worsens with exposure to cold temperatures. Examination shows a 6-mm, blue-red papule under the left thumbnail. The overlying area is extremely tender to palpation. The thumbnail is slightly pitted and cracked. This lesion most likely developed from which of the following types of cells?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Dysplastic melanocytes"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Capillary endothelial cells"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Modified smooth muscle cells"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Hyperpigmented fibroblasts"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Basal epidermal cells"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z409fc6a3e32d11acbee6f0b5c89913e1\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z409fc6a3e32d11acbee6f0b5c89913e1\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\" data-sememe-id=\"18a2lm\">Dysplastic</a></span> <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z016f986cc1b600634610d0dd41cafeba\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z016f986cc1b600634610d0dd41cafeba\" data-section-id=\"otc0eV0\" data-sememe-id=\"y4bdNF\">melanocytes</a></span> are characteristic of a <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=6k0jKT&anker=Z284ff3024f1fef6b53d273100d2b25d0\" data-learningcard-id=\"6k0jKT\" data-anker=\"Z284ff3024f1fef6b53d273100d2b25d0\" data-section-id=\"CwcqOe0\" data-sememe-id=\"7Ba4XM\">dysplastic nevus</a></span> or <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qk0CKT&anker=Z2a98fff73567bff33a5e07c815ae50e4\" data-learningcard-id=\"qk0CKT\" data-anker=\"Z2a98fff73567bff33a5e07c815ae50e4\" data-sememe-id=\"8UbOUG\">melanoma</a></span>. These lesions can uncommonly develop under the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z8561c08e2a18efd66e73473f4b441978\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z8561c08e2a18efd66e73473f4b441978\" data-section-id=\"ptcLeV0\">nail</a> (e.g., <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qk0CKT&anker=Z80062401948d630db7421fe4bc90ca83\" data-learningcard-id=\"qk0CKT\" data-anker=\"Z80062401948d630db7421fe4bc90ca83\" data-section-id=\"hXWcBP0\" data-sememe-id=\"9UaN2P\">acral lentiginous melanoma</a></span>) but are not typically painful or sensitive to cold temperatures.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_547f3a550a77d.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>An asymmetric, pigmented lesion with irregular borders and color variegation is visible over the left little finger.</p><p>These are characteristic features of an atypical nevus.</p></div></div></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z1da3c0a111a5ba00d53ca8601d7a4497\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z1da3c0a111a5ba00d53ca8601d7a4497\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\" data-sememe-id=\"SGcyAd0\">Hemangiomas</a> are comprised of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ZK0ZUS&anker=Zccc525184d694d883090fca453c06718\" data-learningcard-id=\"ZK0ZUS\" data-anker=\"Zccc525184d694d883090fca453c06718\" data-section-id=\"dJcoGW0\">capillary</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Io0YWS&anker=Z5497a0f4058d523c955929ca6a14200a\" data-learningcard-id=\"Io0YWS\" data-anker=\"Z5497a0f4058d523c955929ca6a14200a\" data-section-id=\"4oc3XW0\" data-sememe-id=\"ElX8Ay\">endothelial</a> cells. <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Eu08G3&anker=Z59bea885811818e6aad0a4718cbb0916\" data-learningcard-id=\"Eu08G3\" data-anker=\"Z59bea885811818e6aad0a4718cbb0916\" data-section-id=\"GcdBdK0\" data-sememe-id=\"-DYDSr\">Cherry hemangiomas</a></span> in adults commonly develop on the trunk and upper extremities as multiple, painless, cherry-red, dome-shaped <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Zdff645c223079108b72a307a8753ec7b\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Zdff645c223079108b72a307a8753ec7b\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"sCatt5\">papules</a></span>; they are not typically found under the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z8561c08e2a18efd66e73473f4b441978\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z8561c08e2a18efd66e73473f4b441978\" data-section-id=\"ptcLeV0\">nail</a>.<br><br><span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Lv0w0R&anker=Zd3761b28a7ef939a7b2e344c99cec357\" data-learningcard-id=\"Lv0w0R\" data-anker=\"Zd3761b28a7ef939a7b2e344c99cec357\" data-section-id=\"tMdXqq0\" data-sememe-id=\"zDYrSr\">Infantile hemangiomas</a></span> are also comprised of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ZK0ZUS&anker=Zccc525184d694d883090fca453c06718\" data-learningcard-id=\"ZK0ZUS\" data-anker=\"Zccc525184d694d883090fca453c06718\" data-section-id=\"dJcoGW0\">capillary</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Io0YWS&anker=Z5497a0f4058d523c955929ca6a14200a\" data-learningcard-id=\"Io0YWS\" data-anker=\"Z5497a0f4058d523c955929ca6a14200a\" data-section-id=\"4oc3XW0\" data-sememe-id=\"ElX8Ay\">endothelial</a> cells and may manifest as blue-red <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Zdff645c223079108b72a307a8753ec7b\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Zdff645c223079108b72a307a8753ec7b\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"sCatt5\">papules</a></span> on the fingers. They are typically not painful and usually involute within a few years.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_5a83280abb8b1.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>Multiple well-demarcated cherry-red papules are distributed on the skin.</p><p>This appearance is characteristic of cherry angiomas.</p></div></div></div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) CORRECT:</h4>\n<span class=\"wichtig\"><b><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oj00YT&anker=Zd856467cc092113054ef31d8ed42dd0d\" data-learningcard-id=\"oj00YT\" data-anker=\"Zd856467cc092113054ef31d8ed42dd0d\" data-sememe-id=\"Xm09Vg\">Glomus tumors</a></b></span> are <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z98519ebae0e17b261f3ee4e6d5779a48\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z98519ebae0e17b261f3ee4e6d5779a48\" data-section-id=\"azXQr00\">benign tumors</a> that arise from <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>modified <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=so0tWS&anker=Z866ed9d8301f816f0335f83c58f7c562\" data-learningcard-id=\"so0tWS\" data-anker=\"Z866ed9d8301f816f0335f83c58f7c562\" data-section-id=\"szct8U0\" data-sememe-id=\"cdXaKC\">smooth muscle cells</a> </b></span>of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oj00YT&anker=Z818d725171c868e5bc58c82794c408f2\" data-learningcard-id=\"oj00YT\" data-anker=\"Z818d725171c868e5bc58c82794c408f2\" data-section-id=\"LmcwT10\" data-sememe-id=\"3dXSpC\">glomus body</a>, which is involved in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Zd705c3204a95c4eb31deb2d7e832d3f6\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Zd705c3204a95c4eb31deb2d7e832d3f6\" data-section-id=\"ftck1V0\" data-sememe-id=\"Qxauw5\">dermal</a> <span class=\"wichtig\"><b><span data-sememe-id=\"iU1J1T0\">thermoregulation</span></b></span>. These tumors classically manifest as small (&lt; 2 cm), solitary, painful, blue-red <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Zdff645c223079108b72a307a8753ec7b\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Zdff645c223079108b72a307a8753ec7b\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"sCatt5\">papules</a> or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Ze562e7aa25e368f0be0c7066c00f0243\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Ze562e7aa25e368f0be0c7066c00f0243\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"YdXnoC\">nodules</a> located on the hand, foot, or under the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z8561c08e2a18efd66e73473f4b441978\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z8561c08e2a18efd66e73473f4b441978\" data-section-id=\"ptcLeV0\">nails</a> in patients 20â€“40 years of age. The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> associated with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oj00YT&anker=Zd856467cc092113054ef31d8ed42dd0d\" data-learningcard-id=\"oj00YT\" data-anker=\"Zd856467cc092113054ef31d8ed42dd0d\" data-sememe-id=\"Xm09Vg\">glomus tumors</a> is characteristically <span data-sememe-id=\"930Nkf\">paroxysmal</span>, severe, and is exacerbated by cold.<br><br>Diagnosis is typically clinical and confirmed by histopathologic examination. Treatment involves surgical excision.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_601d5ccd74930.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>A solitary vascularized subcutaneous nodule is visible on the pulp of the little finger of the left hand.</p></div></div></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<span data-sememe-id=\"U6Xb4_\">Hyperpigmented</span> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ro0fWS&anker=Za4a8b0444de65a37fb689ea9c7ee3b47\" data-learningcard-id=\"ro0fWS\" data-anker=\"Za4a8b0444de65a37fb689ea9c7ee3b47\" data-section-id=\"MocMcW0\" data-sememe-id=\"9GbNYv\">fibroblasts</a> are characteristic of a <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Eu08G3&anker=Z58795e24e3f1a635f0cb49054809d9ee\" data-learningcard-id=\"Eu08G3\" data-anker=\"Z58795e24e3f1a635f0cb49054809d9ee\" data-section-id=\"FcdgVK0\" data-sememe-id=\"PBaWaM\">dermatofibroma</a></span>, which typically manifests as an asymptomatic, brown <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Zdff645c223079108b72a307a8753ec7b\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Zdff645c223079108b72a307a8753ec7b\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"sCatt5\">papule</a></span> on the lower extremities with characteristic central dimpling when pinched (<span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Eu08G3&anker=Zc02b804d3afb776c0e003ac799bf6778\" data-learningcard-id=\"Eu08G3\" data-anker=\"Zc02b804d3afb776c0e003ac799bf6778\" data-section-id=\"FcdgVK0\" data-sememe-id=\"4Ba3aM\">dimple sign</a></span>); they are not typically found under the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z8561c08e2a18efd66e73473f4b441978\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z8561c08e2a18efd66e73473f4b441978\" data-section-id=\"ptcLeV0\">nail</a>.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_58a6ce12a3b39.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>A solitary, pigmented, firm circular lesion is visible. Upon pinching of the lesion, the overlaying skin retracts inwards (dimple sign).</p><p>This appearance is suggestive of a dermatofibroma, which usually manifests as a nodule.</p></div></div></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>Abnormal growth of basal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Zf73baeaff6ac94b7f4e9d771060c81d2\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Zf73baeaff6ac94b7f4e9d771060c81d2\" data-section-id=\"ftck1V0\" data-sememe-id=\"exaxv5\">epidermal</a> cells can cause <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rk0f6T&anker=Z7203c5fd9165b5cac35a2e0909331ba1\" data-learningcard-id=\"rk0f6T\" data-anker=\"Z7203c5fd9165b5cac35a2e0909331ba1\" data-sememe-id=\"VM0Gng\">basal cell carcinomas</a></span> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rk0f6T&anker=Z7203c5fd9165b5cac35a2e0909331ba1\" data-learningcard-id=\"rk0f6T\" data-anker=\"Z7203c5fd9165b5cac35a2e0909331ba1\" data-sememe-id=\"VM0Gng\">BCC</a>), which can uncommonly manifest as a pigmented lesion. However, BCCs typically develop in older individuals with an extensive history of sun exposure as a nodular, nontender lesion with a rolled border and central <span data-sememe-id=\"SAcyQU0\">ulceration</span>. BCCs are not typically found under the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z8561c08e2a18efd66e73473f4b441978\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z8561c08e2a18efd66e73473f4b441978\" data-section-id=\"ptcLeV0\">nail</a> and they are not associated with cold <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ps0LDh&anker=Z252fcd07b99eb21a8bff067bee67fd9d\" data-learningcard-id=\"ps0LDh\" data-anker=\"Z252fcd07b99eb21a8bff067bee67fd9d\" data-section-id=\"EfW8Lk0\" data-sememe-id=\"wkXhJy\">sensitivity</a>.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_54106a0bcdd05.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>A red-brown plaque with nodules is visible on an area of skin from the patient's upper thigh. The lesion exhibits both irregular (left) and well-defined borders (right). The surface of the lesion is shiny. Brown melanin pigmentation can also be seen.</p></div></div></div>",
      "hint": "This patient's tender blue-red lesion under the left thumbnail, with pain that worsens with exposure to cold temperatures, suggests a glomus tumor.",
